<br>
Let me give you a quick definition of balance in pvp.  First off any idea of precise balance in pvp is futile.  What we're looking for is a fun aproximation.  <br>
<br>
Pvp between any 2 given classes is balanced when pvp is fun and challenging between them. One party may be favored offensively or defensively but not to the extent that either party feels like they are wasting their time.  Some lvl of difference is fun...its called a challenge.  Past a certain lvl of challenge it because BS and unfun. Take any class at 60 vs a 60 sk as an example of that.<br>
<br>
I don't think rogues are unbalanced vs any class at all though we are I think strong vs wizards.<br>
<br>
The 66% dmg nerf is fair entirely in wizard vs rogue pvp.  If you haven't noticed my suggestions in the thread 45 people looked at but nobody cared to reply to include a suggestion for adjusting that on a class by class , lvl range by lvl range basis btw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/02 12:59:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I understand what yoursaying but..</span><hr size=1> I understand your point in making PvP reasonable for all involved.  A note on this:<br>
